## 9. System Architecture — Component Responsibilities

### 9.1 Component Map
```
C++ Agent (on machine) → Server/Backend → React UI (browser)
    │                         │                 │
    │ Writes log files        │ Serves files    │ Parses + Renders
    │ to local disk           │ via API         │ via Web Worker
    └─────────────────────────┘                 │
                                                └── Parser (Web Worker)
                                                └── Gantt/Bar Charts
                                                └── Settings Modal
```

### 9.2 Parsing: Client-Side Web Worker
- **CONFIRMED**: Parser runs on the UI side in a Web Worker (not on server)
- Handles ~5 MB filtered log files
- Generic: no hardcoded operation names, uses JSON field detection (`lensId`/`spacerId`/`barrelId`)
- Two-pass algorithm: Pass 1 (collect receipts) → Pass 2 (assign operations)

### 9.3 Ideal Time: UI Settings Modal
- User configures ideal times per operation type
- Stored in `localStorage` (or server-side config endpoint)
- Compared against actual `endTs - startTs` for green/red candle coloring
- `idealMs` field in logs is temporary; will be removed eventually

