## 11. C++ Code — Key Bug Fixes Verified ✅

### 11.1 Out-of-Bounds Barrel Fix
- **Before**: `SqBarrelAlignInspectionStart` could proceed even when `_cur_barrel_id >= _barrel_info->size()`
- **After**: Bounds check moved to `SqBarrelAlignInspectionCurrentPosCheck`. `StartTime()` is now called AFTER the bounds check, preventing logging a start for a nonexistent barrel.
- **Location**: [SeqBarrel.cpp](file:///c:/Projects/MODAL%20MANAGEMENT/Github%20Code/6%20apr%20latest/FactoryMonitoring/Seq/SeqBarrel.cpp) — user manually moved the code

### 11.2 Generic Field Names in SeqStepLogger
- All operation-specific names (`lensTopAlignId`, `lensPickupId`, etc.) replaced with generic `lensId`, `spacerId`, `barrelId`
- **Location**: [SeqStepLogger.cpp](file:///c:/Projects/MODAL%20MANAGEMENT/Github%20Code/6%20apr%20latest/FactoryMonitoring/Seq/SeqStepLogger.cpp) lines 86-100

### 11.3 NG JSON Fix
- `SetFailTime()` now properly closes JSON with `\"}` (line 208)
- `ngPath` and `ngCode` values are properly double-quoted
- **Location**: [SeqStepLogger.cpp](file:///c:/Projects/MODAL%20MANAGEMENT/Github%20Code/6%20apr%20latest/FactoryMonitoring/Seq/SeqStepLogger.cpp) lines 123-209

### 11.4 Counter Persistence
- `_lens_top_align_counter` in SeqLens — never reset (confirmed: no reset code exists for this counter)
- `_spacer_pick_id` in SeqSpacer — never reset (confirmed: no FinishTray for spacer)
- `_cur_barrel_id` in SeqBarrel — resets to 0 in `FinishTray()` (correct behavior)

