## 12. Duration Calculation Formulas

### 12.1 Operation Duration
```
Duration = endTs - startTs  (from JSON metadata)
```

### 12.2 Barrel Duration (Candle Height)
```
Duration = MAX(endTs of all operations in this barrel) - MIN(startTs of all operations in this barrel)
```
This includes pre-fetched parallel operations. The candle represents the total wall-clock footprint.

### 12.3 Tray Duration (Candle Height)
```
Duration = MAX(endTs of last barrel's last op) - MIN(startTs of first barrel's first op)
```
Will eventually include Load_Tray/Unload_Tray once those logs are added.

### 12.4 Green/Red Comparison
```
if (actualDuration < userConfiguredIdealTime) → GREEN candle
if (actualDuration >= userConfiguredIdealTime) → RED candle
```

